text.__SUMMARY__: Melanella conoidea is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Eulimidae. The species is one of many species known to exist within the genus, Melanella.
text.Distribution:
This species occurs in the following locations:
Caribbean Sea
Colombia
Costa Rica
Cuba
Gulf of Mexico
Lesser Antilles
Mexico
Puerto Rico
Venezuela
text.Description: The maximum recorded shell length is 12.7 mm.
text.Habitat: Minimum recorded depth is 0 m. Maximum recorded depth is 538 m.
